from /public/docs/wizard/shop
*****************************************************************************
This is documentation to explain creating a shop, using the shop inheritable.
The new setup of any shop, will remove the backroom of the shop.  There is a
storing object, that is left in the void.  You do not need to do anything for
this to occur.

In every shop you must:
  #include <mudlib.h>
  #include <treasure.h
  #include <material.h>
  #include <types.h>
  inherit SHOP;         --> for the shop room.

Do not inherit ROOM, SHOP does that already.

There are a few functions which you have to define: (preferably in this order)

set_shop_ob(this_object());
  Setup the shop for this particular object.

set_value_info( ({ ({ 200, 20 }), ({ 400, 17 }), ({ 600, 15 }),
                   ({ 800, 13 }), ({ 1000, 11}), ({ 1400, 9 }),
                   ({ 1500, 7 }), ({ 2000, 5 }), ({ 2500, 4 }),
                   ({ 3000, 3 }), ({ 3500, 2 }), ({ 4000, 1 }) }) );

  This function is used to set up how many similar items of a certain value
  the shop will keep.  (Although it will still buy more than its max value,
  it will not keep them, but it will destruct them.)  In the above example,
  the shop will keep 20 items worth less than 200, 17 items less than 400,
  etc, etc, 3 items less than 3000, 2 items less than 3500 and 1 item less
  than 4000.  Items worth more than 4000 will be destructed.  The syntax
  of the function is as follows, a 2 dimensional array (many arrays, within
  on large array.)

setup();
  Setup this object.

set_shopkeep(string str, string filename);
  str = name of the shopkeeper.  filename = filename of the shopkeeper.
  set_shopkeep("shopkeep","players/myname/shopkeep_guy");
  NOTE: Do _NOT_ put a '/' up front of the "players" in this string.

set_guard(string str, string filename);
  str = name of the guard.  filename = filename of the guard for that shop,
        that's called if the shop is robbed.
  set_storeroom("players/myname/guard");
  NOTE: Do _NOT_ put a '/' up front of the "players" in this string.

set_shop_type(int arg);
  arg = the bits which you are setting for the type of weapons and armours
        this shop will buy.  You can set ALLTYPES for all armour and
        weapons.
  set_shop_type(ALLTYPES);
  set_shop_type(HELMET|LARGE|BOOTS|SMALL);
  set_shop_type(~PLATE);  // all types except plate

set_shop_t_type(int iArg);
  iArg = the bits which you are setting for the type of treasures this shop
        will buy.  You can set TYP_ALLTREASURES for all of them.
  set_shop_t_type(TYP_JEWELRY|TYP_FURNITURE);

set_shop_material(int iArg);
  iArg = the bits which you are setting for the material of objects this shop
        will buy.  You can set ALLMATERIALS for all materials.
  set_shop_material(MAT_GOLD|MAT_SILVER|MAT_COPPER);

set_mat_spec(int arg);
  arg = the bits which you set that the player can sell items of that material
        for full value, not 1/2.  This includes the material of that item.
  set_mat_spec(MAT_STEEL|MAT_MITHRIL);

set_typ_spec(int iArg);
  iArg = the bits which you set that the player can sell items of that type
        for full value, not 1/2.
  set_typ_spec(HELMET|GLOVES);

set_t_typ_spec(int iArg);
  iArg = the bits for the treasure types that the player can sell for full value
  set_t_type_spec(TYP_BONES|TYP_MAP);

set_typ_exclude(int iArg);
set_t_typ_exclude(int iArg);
set_mat_exclude(int iArg);
  iArg = a type, treasure type, or material that you want the shop totally
        barred from buying at all, regardless of anything else that is
        allowed.  For example, a treasure of type TYP_GEM|TYP_BOOK
        would normally be sellable at a shop that takes TYP_BOOK, but
        not if you
  set_t_type_exclude(TYP_GEM);

NOTE:  You can set all of the bitfield functions again and again. The final
       value will be the total bitfield you have passed, it 'ors' all the
       passes together.

set_sell();
  Call this function to tell the inheritable that your shop will sell items.

set_buy();
  Call this function to tell the inheritable that your shop will buy items.

add_stock(string filename, int number);
  This is just like add_clone.  However, it puts these items in the store
  object upon updating.  You can have multiple add_stock() functions.

restock();
  This stocks the store.

  Note:  With add_stock and restock, you obviously want to restock the store
         after your add_stock lines, preferably only once per reboot.

There are a few functions already in the init of SHOP.
You do not need to add_action these.
  list:
    - will list the items in the store.
  sell:
    - will allow the player to sell any thing they have, provided the shop
      buys that type of item.  If the it is a specialty item, they will get
      full price for it.
  buy:
    - will alloy the player to buy anything from the shop, provided they have
      the money, and they can carry it.
  value:
    - will value anything on the player, and in the room, telling them what
      they would get if they sold that item.
  read:
    - lets the player read the bounty list.
  rob:
    - lets a thief rob the store.
  loot_me:
    - will tell you how much cash the shop currently has.
*****************************************************************************
Below is an example of a general store that buys and sells anything.  It buys
all items at half the set value except for MITHRIL items and GLOVES, which it
pays full value for.


#include <mudlib.h>
#include <treasure.h>
#include <material.h>
#include <types.h>
#include "hyper.h"
inherit SHOP;

void reset(int iArg)
{
   if(iArg) return;
   ::reset(iArg);
   set_terrain("city");
   add_terrain("inside");
   set_domain("hyperborea");
   set_light(1);
   set_short("Ivar's Northern Outfitters");
   set_long("\
A large fire burns in a fireplace along the north wall.  The windows\n\
of this log building are shuttered against the howling wind and\n\
freezing temperatures.  Tables and shelves are scattered about the\n\
store where goods may be found.\n\
Commands: <LIST {items}>, <BUY {item}>, <VALUE {item}>, or <SELL {item}>\n");
   set_shop_ob(this_object());
   set_value_info( ({ ({ 200, 20 }), ({ 400, 17 }), ({ 600, 15 }),
                      ({ 800, 13 }), ({ 1000,11 }), ({ 1400, 9 }),
                      ({ 1500, 7 }), ({ 2000, 5 }), ({ 2500, 4 }),
                      ({ 3000, 3 }), ({ 3500, 2 }), ({ 4000, 1 }) }) );
   setup();
   set_shopkeep("shopkeep",HYPER + "monsters/ivar");
   set_guard("guard",HYPER + "monsters/guard");
   set_shop_type(ALLTYPES)             <-- half price for all items
   set_shop_t_type(TYP_ALLTREASURES);  <-- half price for all items
   set_shop_material(ALLMATERIALS);    <-- half price for all materials
   set_mat_spec(MITHRIL);              <----  full price for mithril items
   set_typ_spec(GLOVES);               <----  full price for gloves
/*
   since they are not set, there are no treasure type specialties,
   and no type is excluded from being bought/sold here
*/
   set_sell();                         <----  you can sell stuff here
   set_buy();                          <----  you can buy stuff here
   add_stock(HYPER + "obj/torch", 2);
   add_stock(HYPER + "obj/furmittens", 2);
   add_stock(HYPER + "obj/furcloak", 2);
   restock();

   add_exit("east", HYPER + "town11");

   add_look(({"fire","fireplace","large fire"}),"\
A large fire burns in the fireplace, keeping the store nice and warm.\n");
   add_look(({"windows","shutters"}),"\
The shutters are closed to keep out the wind and the cold.\n");
   add_look(({"tables","shelves","store"}),"\
There is a lot of stuff here.\n");
}

